Sentencas: The effect of tungsten addition to Fe-22Cr-0.5Mn ferritic stainless steel on the oxidation, electric property and Cr evaporation is investigated for application to the solid oxide fuel cell interconnects.
Titulo: Oxide modification by chi phase formed on oxide/metal interface of Fe-22Cr-0.5Mn ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: The mass gain, area specific resistance and Cr evaporation rate are evaluated to examine the feasibility of these alloys for an interconnect material.
Titulo: Oxide modification by chi phase formed on oxide/metal interface of Fe-22Cr-0.5Mn ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: Addition of 4-6 wt.% W reduces the oxidation rate, evaporation rate of Cr vapor species and area specific resistance of Fe-22Cr-0.5Mn steel.
Titulo: Oxide modification by chi phase formed on oxide/metal interface of Fe-22Cr-0.5Mn ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: When more than 4 wt.% W is added, chi (chi) phase particles are formed, especially beneath the interface between the oxide layer and substrate steel.
Titulo: Oxide modification by chi phase formed on oxide/metal interface of Fe-22Cr-0.5Mn ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: These second phase particles are responsible for suppressing the fast diffusion of Cr, so that the surface Cr content is reduced while Mn content is increased.
Titulo: Oxide modification by chi phase formed on oxide/metal interface of Fe-22Cr-0.5Mn ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: This reduction in Cr content at the surface is responsible for the lower Cr evaporation rate and area specific resistance.
Titulo: Oxide modification by chi phase formed on oxide/metal interface of Fe-22Cr-0.5Mn ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect
